article.headline: Lehigh 70, American 59
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Jose Olivero scored 22 points, leading Lehigh to a 70-59 victory at American on Saturday. Bryan White added 14 points and Kyle Neptune had 10 for the Mountain Hawks (8-8, 1-0) in their third straight victory. Olivero fouled out late in the second half. Down 48-47 with 7:00 to play, Lehigh sprang a 14-6 run, capped by back-to-back 3-pointers from Olivero and Mitch Gilfillan that made it 63-54. Arvydas Eitutavicius scored 15 points off the bench for American (4-9, 0-1), including a 3-pointer from the top of the arc that gave the Eagles their only second half lead. Andre Ingram added 11. Lehigh led at 31-28 at the half after American committed 11 turnovers, part of 19 total. Eitutavicius and the rest of the bench kept the Eagles close with 18 first-half points. Lehigh committed just nine turnovers in American's first home loss. ^
